result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Tommie Lee Young Jr was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. miscConds.notes: Fine ($3,039) to be paid as a Condition of Probation.

DNA surcharge ($250) to be paid as a Condition of Probation.  Reimbursement for Blood Draw costs ($35) to be paid/forwarded to Waukesha Co Clerk of Courts for Delafield Police Department and to be paid as a Condition of Probation.

  If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling.
AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended.

ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
Submit to random urine screens.
No use or possession of alcohol, illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.
No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of any and all prescriptions.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged and distributed.
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (for example, bars, taverns or liquor stores).
Ignition Interlock Device installed for the period of Probation.
Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel during the period of Probation.
Not to drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.
The Court recommends the Department of Corrections supervise the defendant in accordance with the standards defined in DOC Administrative Directive 10-04.
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided.

Defendant Tommie Lee Young in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph Smith.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in.  Count 3 is dismissed by operation of law.  
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 0 days);
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S); Probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).
*Ignition Interlock Device installed for the period of probation.  
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel during the period of probation.
*Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license.
*The court recommends the Department of Corrections supervise the defendant in accordance with the standards defined in DOC Administrative Directive 10-04.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to Delafield Police Department);

FINE:  $3039 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  6 MONTHS -  NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions, Apply 71 days credit.  To commence forthwith. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
